{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = Encyclopedia of the Consumer Movement | image = Encyclopedia of the consumer movement.jpg | caption = | author = 168 authors, [[Stephen Brobeck]] is editor | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = | series = | subject = [[Consumer movement]] | genre = [[Reference work]] | publisher = [[ABC-CLIO]] | pub_date = 1997 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 274 | isbn = 0-87436-987-8 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = HC79.C63E53 1997 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
The '''''Encyclopedia of the Consumer Movement''''' is a 1997 [[encyclopedia]] edited by [[Stephen Brobeck]] and which describes the history of the [[consumer movement]] and other topics related to [[consumerism]].
==Synopsis== The work contains 198 entries written by 168 authors.<ref name="Carsky">{{cite journal|last=Carsky|first=Mary L.|title=Encyclopedia of the Consumer Movement|journal=Journal of Public Policy & Marketing|date=Spring 1999|volume=18|issue=1|pages=130–133|pmid=|url=https://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/30000516?uid=3739832}}</ref> The scope is the history, activities, interests, legislation, and actors in the twentieth century consumer movement.<ref name="Carsky"/> Focuses of the work include 40 articles each describing the consumer movement in a different country, various articles on specific actions undertaken by consumer activists, and descriptions of the interests of specific populations or demographics in the consumer movement.<ref name="Carsky"/>
The authors include established persons from academia, government, activism, and regulatory organizations who wrote entries summarizing their own fields of expertise.<ref name="Apple">{{cite journal|last=Apple|first=Rima D.|title=Encyclopedia of the Consumer Movement|journal=[[Journal of Consumer Affairs]]|date=Dec 22, 1999|volume=33|issue=2|page=438|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Encyclopedia+of+the+Consumer+Movement.-a064059261}}</ref>
==Reviews== One reviewer called the work "the only comprehensive reference source of its kind."<ref name="Carsky"/> Another said that "In its depth, breadth, scholarship, and readability, this volume will be considered the standard reference source for many years".<ref name="Apple"/>
